Defending champions Ebun Comets look set to crash out of the ongoing Crown Elite Basketball Championship, after losing their second consecutive game at the event, which began on Tuesday at the Indoor Sports Hall of the National Stadium, Lagos. Comets were comprehensively beaten 63-36 by University of Lagos on Wednesday, after their opening day defeat to Kwara Falcons in Group A of the competition, leaving them with no points. They are bottom of the pool, while Lagos Islanders top the group with maximum six points after edging Falcons 52-48 on Day 2. Rivers Hoopers brightened their chances of advancing from Group B, beating Raptors 65-47, following Tuesday’s defeat to Lagos Legends. Leaders Lagos Legends punished Dodan Warriors 75-39 for their second consecutive victory, leaving Warriors without a point and bottom of the log. On Thursday (today) Raptors eye an end to Legends’ unbeaten run, with Hoopers hoping to compound Warriors woes in Group B. In Group A, Comets target their first win against high-flying Islanders, with Falcons engaging UNILAG in a tricky tie.  Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com